The paper deals with problems related to wireless networks and distributed storage systems, which are both subfields of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial algorithms and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AL (Algorithms) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem of channel assignment in wireless networks is related to graph coloring, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the problem of data migration in heterogeneous storage systems could be classified under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
